History & Key Milestones
Dymon Asia Capital, co-founded in 2008 by Danny Yong and Keith Tan, is a leading Asia focused alternative investment management firm. The firm’s first product, which would evolve into the flagship and cornerstone of today’s business, is a macro focused fund vehicle which was initially launched with US$100 million in seed capital from Tudor Investment Corporation and US$13 million in proprietary monies.
As of June 1, 2017 assets under management (AUM) across hedge fund, private equity and venture capital strategies are approximately US$5.7 billion (included committed capital and notional assets).
Dymon Asia Capital is proud to be majority owned by its Partner employees. The firm has over 100 employees. Headquarters are located in Singapore with offices in Hong Kong, Malaysia and the United Kingdom.
Our Key Milestones:


August 2009: Dymon Asia Macro Fund is launched




February 2012: Ranked 7th best performing global hedge fund of 2011 by Bloomberg




March 2012: Dymon Asia Macro Fund AUM reaches US$2.5 billion




October 2012: Dymon Asia Private Equity (S.E. Asia) Fund, L.P launches with a commitment from Heliconia Capital Management, a wholly owned subsidiary of Temasek Holdings




May 2014: A partnership with Temasek is formed. Temasek commits US$500 million to establish the Dymon Manager Solutions Group, becoming a stakeholder in Dymon Asia Capital




December 2014: Ranked 10th best performing global hedge fund of 2014 by Bloomberg




August 2015: Dymon Asia Ventures is launched








































